name: The Dreamer
author: Amigo The Devil
lyrics:
I'm so God damn tired of whistling. I'm so lonesome I could cry.
Your eyes, they look like diamonds, still stuck inside the mines.
I'll dig 'em out.
And I know that you're waiting around to find the right man, you say.
But the thing about taking your time is it takes it right back, some day.
No one deserves my world quite like you do.
And it's true, I hate everything but you.
So tonight I'll follow you home
Drag my  lips up your thighs, wait 'till you open your eyes
And I'll hold you real still.
And if I can't have you, nobody will.
Winter was leaving early, that chill to the bone.
And I kissed you every morning, as the wind whistled on.
But God's humour did too.
When you're as happy as this, time starts to fly, it's true.
But I built these wings after jumping, not dreaming of the sky for you.
And it's all for you.
My skin is grey too.
And I'll lay by your side 'till everything is rotten through.
So tonight we'll celebrate life.
Make love too. Dreaming every moment of you,
Your chest against mine. My gun against your spine.
And we'll leave the world the way dreamers do.
And it's all for you.
It's all for you.
These things that I do.
They're all for you.
My skin is grey too.
It's all for you.
And I'll lay by your side 'till everything is rotten through.
